## C. Recommended UML Relationships (<<include>> and <<extend>>)

To properly construct the UML diagram, apply these structural relationships.

### `<<include>>` (Mandatory usage/reuse)
*   `Book Service` **<<include>>** `Check Time-Slot Availability` *(You cannot book without checking slots).*
*   `Secure Digital Payment` **<<include>>** `Process Chapa Transaction`.
*   `Complete Service Task` **<<include>>** `Generate Final Invoice`.
*   `Generate Final Invoice` **<<include>>** `Calculate Inventory Usage`.
*   `Register User / Login` **<<include>>** `Authenticate Credentials`.

### `<<extend>>` (Optional, conditional, or exceptional flows)
*   `Login` **<-- <<extend>> --** `Reset Password (Forgot Password)` *(Only happens if the user forgets).*
*   `Book Service` **<-- <<extend>> --** `Request Emergency Prioritization` *(Only if the user ticks 'Is Emergency').*
*   `Track Vehicle Status` **<-- <<extend>> --** `Cancel Booking` *(Customer realizes they can't make it).*
*   `Track Vehicle Status` **<-- <<extend>> --** `Approve Repair Estimate` *(Only triggered if cost exceeds original quote).*
*   `Update Repair Progress` **<-- <<extend>> --** `Request Spare Parts` *(Only if parts run out mid-job).*
*   `Secure Digital Payment` **<-- <<extend>> --** `Process Payment Refund` *(Only happens on failure/cancellation).*

### Actor Generalization (Inheritance)
*   `Garage Manager` **--|>** `Garage Staff`
*   `Garage Owner` **--|>** `Garage Staff` 
*   *(Both inherit the ability to "Manage Inventory", "Manage Bookings", preventing diagram clutter).*
*   `Super Admin` **--|>** `System Administrator`

