## D. Diagram Readiness & Final Corrected Use Case List

**Diagram Readiness Verdict:** *Previously Not Ready. Now Ready.* 
Without explicitly mapping the `<<include>>` and `<<extend>>` dependencies, the diagram would have been too bloated with flat use cases, losing marks for architectural depth. 

Here is the **Academic-Ready Use Case List** mapped by Actor:

### Human Actors
**1. Customer**
*   Login / Register User
*   Manage Vehicle Profile
*   Search Garages *(External: Location API)*
*   Book Service
    *   *<<include>> Check Time-Slot Availability*
    *   *<<extend>> Request Emergency Prioritization*
*   Reschedule Booking
*   Cancel Booking
*   Track Vehicle Status
    *   *<<extend>> Approve Repair Estimate*
*   Secure Digital Payment
    *   *<<include>> Process Chapa Transaction*
*   Leave Review & Rating
*   Submit Quality Complaint

**2. Mechanic**
*   Receive & Accept Assigned Task
*   Update Repair Progress
    *   *<<extend>> Request Spare Parts*
*   Estimate Repair Cost & Time
*   Complete Service Task
*   View Service History

**3. Garage Staff (Abstract - Inherited by Owner & Manager)**
*   Manage Bookings & Assign Mechanics
*   Process Walk-in Customer
*   Manage Service Catalog 
*   Manage Parts Inventory

**4. Garage Manager (Inherits Garage Staff)**
*   Manage Service Queue (Waitlist)
*   Configure Mechanic Skills

**5. Garage Owner (Inherits Garage Staff)**
*   Delegate Management (Hire Managers)
*   View Executive Analytics

**6. Accountant**
*   Generate Final Invoice
    *   *<<include>> Calculate Inventory Usage*
*   View Financial Analytics

**7. Super Admin**
*   Manage Garages (Register / Deactivate)
*   Resolve Customer Complaints
*   Perform System Backup
    *   *<<extend>> Restore System Backup*

### Non-Human Actors
**8. System (Timer/Scheduler)**
*   Send Service Reminders *(External: Email/SMS API)*
*   Notify Low Stock
*   Auto-Cancel Expired Pending Bookings

**9. Chapa Payment API**
*   Process Chapa Transaction
*   Process Payment Refund

**10. Location / Maps API**
*   Provide Proximity Coordinates (Search)
